if you were allowed to rewind or replay segment of your past what would that be and if you could undo one which would that be there are most like more than one however at the moment when i read this one came into my mind my father was injured in a plane crash that ultimately killed him my mother was staying at my house going to and from the hospital everyday i had a small daughter and in the morning i received a phone called that my dad was passing my mom left with my husband immediately but when i called they told me to wait and not bring my daughter it was close to his death and not a place for her so i waited at home to hear of the death of my dadt i would never do that again i don't care what anyone would think i would drag myself and my screaming baby girl to be there with my dad even if he never knew i was there at least i would of and even if they didnt want my girl there remember always sometimes it is too late to say good bye and thank you never let an opportunity pass you by yes this i would change if i could do what you know is right for you in your heart not what other people tell you to do you have to live with yourself the rest of you life Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Jon Secada Pitaten Phoebe Buffay's songs Father's Day (Doctor Who) Miss Saigon The Shining (film) About a Boy Neighbours Shaggy dog story Social rule Kill Bill Days of our Lives Rovers Return Journey (band) Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Scenes from a Memory Knots Landing The Marshall Mathers LP Little Girl Lost (The Twilight Zone) Rais massacre The Inside Mr. and Mrs. Turner Silent Night, Deadly Night United Airlines Flight 93 Kyle Broflovski Milton H. Erickson StarCraft: Uprising One Life to Live Grandview, U.S.A. Sleeping Murder Ron and Fez The Lovely Bones EastEnders Joke The Subtle Knife Hollyoaks Daredevil Friends Night (book) Theory of conduct Odysseus Laura Schlessinger The Amber Spyglass Jacques-Louis David September 11, 2001 attacks timeline for the day of the attacks The 